ocus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532487\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tre1665702780948.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tre1665702780948.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tre1665702780948.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tre1665702780948\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Migration of Subtype Properties\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Values of properties that cannot be specialized in subtype entities or components are cleared during migration.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tre1665702780948__p_d69041e1_d69042e1_d69043e1\">In Uniface 10, subtype entities can inherit properties from their supertypes. This is new functionality.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tre1665702780948__p_d69044e1_d69045e1_d69046e1\">In Uniface 9, this behavior was simulated to a limited extent by copying values when the subtype was created. However, for most properties, subsequent changes to supertype properties were not inherited.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tre1665702780948__p_d69047e1_d69048e1_d69049e1\">To ensure compatibility, the Migration Utility does not remove the copied property values, with the exception of properties that cannot be specialized on subtypes or in component entities. If data is found in properties that cannot be specialized, either in a subtype entity or a component, the Migration Utility will clear the values of these properties to prevent confusion. The following properties are cleared:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tre1665702780948__li_d31487e1_d31488e1_d31489e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mcg1665702702535.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mcg1665702702535.html\" title=\"Determines whether the entity is stored in a database. If N, the Data Access and Database Path property values are ignored.\">Database Behavior</a> (Entity)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tre1665702780948__li_d31490e1_d31491e1_d31492e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jlp1665702702609.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jlp1665702702609.html\" title=\"Defines how an entity will access the data store—via a database path, or via an entity service.\">Data Access</a> (Entity)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tre1665702780948__li_d31493e1_d31494e1_d31495e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cyp1665702702678.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cyp1665702702678.html\" title=\"DBMS path to use when storing occurrences of this entity. This is a named route to the Uniface DBMS connector used to connect to the database. Valid values are Uniface default paths ($DEF, $SYS, $UUU), supported databases and file formats, and user-defined paths. The default is DEF.\">Database Path</a> (Entity)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tre1665702780948__li_d31496e1_d31497e1_d31498e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"enu1665702584272.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/enu1665702584272.html\" title=\"This property (also known as the entity interface) determines how the data is mapped to the database.\">Database Interface (Entities)</a> (Entity and Field)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tre1665702780948__li_d31499e1_d31500e1_d31501e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aww1665702586248.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aww1665702586248.html\" title=\"Uniface data type to use for this field, variable, or parameter. The default value is S (String).\">Data Type</a> (Field)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tre1665702780948__li_d31502e1_d31503e1_d31504e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pta1665702586322.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pta1665702586322.html\" title=\"Determines whether the Field's data can be externalized outside the component, either by storing it in a database or passing it in an entity or occurrence parameter.\">Is External</a> (Field)\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tre1665702780948__p_d69050e1_d69051e1_d69052e1\">To enable other properties to inherit from their supertype, you must manually remove the copied values in the subtype entities.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532487\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532487\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Migration of Subtype Properties Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Migration of Subtype Properties Values of properties that cannot be specialized in subtype entities or components are cleared during migration. In Uniface 10, subtype entities can inherit properties from their supertypes. This is new functionality. In Uniface 9, this behavior was simulated to a limited extent by copying values when the subtype was created. However, for most properties, subsequent changes to supertype properties were not inherited. To ensure compatibility, the Migration Utility does not remove the copied property values, with the exception of properties that cannot be specialized on subtypes or in component entities. If data is found in properties that cannot be specialized, either in a subtype entity or a component, the Migration Utility will clear the values of these properties to prevent confusion. The following properties are cleared: Database Behavior (Entity) Data Access (Entity) Database Path (Entity) Database Interface (Entities) (Entity and Field) Data Type (Field) Is External (Field) To enable other properties to inherit from their supertype, you must manually remove the copied values in the subtype entities. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}